        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 20 at 3:48PM MDT until June 20 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Prairie County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 445 PM MDT.

* At 347 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles northeast
of Miles City, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Mildred.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with this storm. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is
one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder,
you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
